  "text": "Mericske-Stern (1997) [CITATION_1] also did a study on 5 patients with two ITI (Straumann) implants each. The mean bite force obtained in the patients was 9.82 kgf. In the study of Mericske-Stern, the mean age of the 11 patients was 74 years, which was 15 years older than the mean age of patients in the present study (59 years). This is thought to be attributed to the different age range of the patients of the two studies. Maximum bite force of conventional denture subjects was only 20 to 40% that of dentate subjects in accordance to previous findings (Helkimo et al, 1977; Haraldson et al, 1979; Slagter et al, 1993; [CITATION_2] .",
